# Resource Forms

## Name & Description

Always use `<ResourceFormHeader>` from `@/components/resource-form-header` for the name/description card on any resource create or edit form (strategies, input presets, prompt versions, etc.).

```tsx
import { ResourceFormHeader, ErrorCard } from '@/components/resource-form-header';

<ResourceFormHeader
  name={name}
  onNameChange={setName}
  namePlaceholder="e.g. Modern bathroom 3-step refinement"
  description={description}
  onDescriptionChange={setDescription}
/>
```

- Renders a white card (`p-5 shadow-xs`) with labeled Name + Description fields
- `nameRequired` defaults to `true` (shows red asterisk)
- Never use raw inline-editable inputs for name/description — always use this card

## Error Display

Use `<ErrorCard>` for all form error messages. Never use bare `<p className="text-red-600">`.

```tsx
{error && <div className="mt-4"><ErrorCard message={error} /></div>}
```

## Page Structure for Create/Edit Forms

1. `<PageHeader>` with back link + save button in actions
2. `<ResourceFormHeader>` for name/description (with `mt-6`)
3. `{error && <ErrorCard />}` (with `mt-4`)
4. Resource-specific fields below

## Page Structure for Resource Lists

Every resource (strategies, input presets, prompt versions, environments) follows the same pattern:

1. **List page** — server component that fetches data, renders `<PageHeader>` with `<PrimaryLinkButton href="/resource/new">`, then `<DataTable>` (or `<EmptyState>` when empty)
2. **Create page** (`/resource/new`) — `<PageHeader>` with back link + `<PrimaryButton>` save action, form fields below
3. **Edit page** (`/resource/[id]/edit`) — server component loads data, passes to a client form component

Never embed create/edit forms inline on the list page. Always use separate routes.
